### ===========================
### PORTFOLIO ENDPOINTS
### ===========================

### Create a new portfolio
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: portfolio object with id, name, description, createdDate, numberOfStocks=0, totalValue=0
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Tech Stocks",
    "description": "My technology investments"
}

###

### Create a second portfolio
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: portfolio object with id=2
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Dividend Stocks",
    "description": "Long term dividend investments"
}

###

### Get all portfolios
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: list of all portfolios
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios

###

### Get portfolio by id
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: single portfolio object with id=1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1

###

### Get portfolio that does not exist
### Expected: 404 Not Found
### Returns: { "status": 404, "message": "Portfolio not found with id: 999", "timestamp": "..." }
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/999

###

### Update a portfolio
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: updated portfolio object with new name
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Tech Giants",
    "description": "Updated description"
}

###

### Try to create portfolio with empty name
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### Returns: { "status": 400, "message": "Portfolio name cannot be empty", "timestamp": "..." }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "",
    "description": "This should fail"
}

###

### ===========================
### STOCK ENDPOINTS
### ===========================

### Add Apple stock to portfolio 1
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: stock object with id, name=AAPL, symbol=AAPL, quantity=10, purchasePrice=189.50
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    
    "symbol": "AAPL",
    "quantity": 10,
    "purchasePrice": 189.50,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-15"
}

###

### Add Tesla stock to portfolio 1
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: stock object with id=2
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "TSLA",
    "quantity": 5,
    "purchasePrice": 220.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-20"
}

###

### Add Google stock to portfolio 2
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: stock object with id=3, portfolioId=2
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/2/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "GOOGL",
    "quantity": 3,
    "purchasePrice": 140.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-02-01"
}

###

### Get all stocks in portfolio 1
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: list containing Apple and Tesla stocks
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks

###

### Get all stocks in portfolio 2
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: list containing only Google stock
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/2/stocks

###

### Get one stock by id
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: Apple stock object
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/1

###

### Try to get stock from wrong portfolio
### Expected: 404 Not Found
### Returns: { "status": 404, "message": "Stock does not belong to portfolio with id: 1", "timestamp": "..." }
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/3

###

### Update a stock
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: updated stock with quantity=20
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "quantity": 20,
    "purchasePrice": 189.50
}

###

### Try to add stock with negative quantity
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### Returns: { "status": 400, "message": "Quantity must be greater than zero", "timestamp": "..." }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "AMZN",
    "quantity": -5,
    "purchasePrice": 150.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-15"
}

###

### Try to add stock with missing symbol
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### Returns: { "status": 400, "message": "Stock symbol cannot be empty", "timestamp": "..." }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "",
    "quantity": 5,
    "purchasePrice": 150.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-15"
}

###

### Delete a stock
### Expected: 204 No Content
### Returns: empty response
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/2

###

### Delete a portfolio (also deletes all its stocks due to cascade)
### Expected: 204 No Content
### Returns: empty response
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/2